### `compare <dateA> <dateB>`: quality report comparison

Execution steps:

1. Read `summary.md` from both date directories. If missing, read and aggregate all round reports under that date directory.
2. Compare P0/P1/P2/P3 counts, release blockers, pre-release must-fix items, high-risk modules, and needs-further-verification items.
3. List newly introduced issues, resolved issues, severity-increased issues, severity-decreased issues, and still-open issues.
4. Match issues by title, file, class, method, and code location. Do not match by title alone.
5. State whether quality improved, worsened, or stayed roughly the same.

